${\footnote $ Keys Reference}
K{\footnote K Keys Reference}
#{\footnote # loc20}
{\b \fs24 Keys Reference}
\par
\pard 
\plain \qj \fs20 \f0 Below is a key-reference.
\par 
Many of the functions are available 
from the pull-down menus, but of course, in the heat of battle 
it is more convenient to invoke them via a key-stroke. 
\par
\par
Unless otherwise indicated, typing an lowercase letter will issue the 
same command as the uppercase letter shown.
\par
\par

{
 \pard \plain \f1 \fs10
{\b \f0 \fs20 Eject! Eject! Eject!}
\par
{\b Q} or {\b <ESC>} ....... Exits the game immediately (use when boss approaches)
\par
\par
{\b \f0 \fs20 Flight Control Keys }
\par
{\b *} ................ 100% throttle
\par
{\b /} ................ 0% throttle
\par
{\b +} ................ increase throttle
\par
{\b -} ................ decrease throttle
\par
{\b W} ................ release/engage wheel brakes
\par
{\b B} ................ release/engage speed brakes
\par
{\b G} ................ raise/lower landing gear
\par
{\b A} ................ engage/disengage {\uldb Autopilot}{\v loc24}
\par
{\b J} ................ left rudder
\par
{\b L} ................ right rudder
\par
{\b K} ................ center rudder
\par
{\b f} ................ flaps down
\par
{\b F} ................ flaps up
\par
{\b t} ................ trim up
\par
{\b T} ................ trim down
\par
{\b <ctl>t} .......... neutral trim
\par
\par
{\b \f0 \fs20 View Keys}
\par
{\b 1} ................ front
\par
{\b 2} ................ left
\par
{\b 3} ................ right
\par
{\b 4} ................ back
\par
Combine above views with {\b SHIFT} to tilt up or {\b CTRL} to tilt down
\par
{\b 5} ................ top
\par
{\b 0} ................ virtual
\par
{\b 6} ................ {\uldb Outside View}{\v loc60}
\par
{\b 7} ................ {\uldb Target Track}{\v loc61}
\par
{\b 8} ................ {\uldb Target Track II}{\v loc62}
\par
{\b 9} ................ flyby
\par
{\b &} ................ padlock
\par 
For virtual and Outside views:
\par
{\b F2} ............... rotate left
\par
{\b F3} ............... rotate right
\par
{\b F4} ............... rotate down
\par
{\b F5} ............... rotate up
\par
{\b F6} ............... snap to front
\par
Numeric keypad views (NumLock on)
\par
{\b NUMPAD8} ......... front
\par
{\b NUMPAD7} ......... front left
\par
{\b NUMPAD9} ......... front right
\par
{\b NUMPAD4} ......... left
\par
{\b NUMPAD6} ......... right
\par
{\b NUMPAD2} ......... rear
\par
{\b NUMPAD1} ......... rear left
\par
{\b NUMPAD3} ......... rear right
\par
Combine above keys with {\b NUMPAD5} to tilt up, {\b NUMPAD0} to tilt down
\par
\par
{\b \f0 \fs20 Cockpit and HUD}
\par
{\b C} ................ Show/hide {\uldb Cockpit Bitmap and Instruments}{\v loc50}
\par
{\b H} ................ Show/hide {\uldb Heads Up Display (HUD)}{\v loc51}
\par
{\b S} ................ Show/hide aircraft externals
\par
{\b V} ................ Show/hide flight-path indicator
\par
{\b <ctrl>Z} ......... Show/hide frame rate display
\par 
\par
{\b \f0 \fs20 Weapons}
\par
{\b X} ................ Arm/disarm selected weapon
\par
{\b <BACKSPACE>} ..... Select next weapon
\par
{\b <SPACEBAR>} ...... Fire selected weapon
\par
\par
{\b \f0 \fs20 Miscellaneous}
\par
{\b <ENTER>} .......... Select Next Target {\uldb See Target Track}{\v loc61}
\par
{\b <TAB>} ............ {\uldb Jump To Next Plane}{\v loc80}
\par
{\b F11} .............. Toggle texture-mapped landscape
\par
{\b F12} .............. Toggle clouds
\par
{\b <ctrl>F} .......... Apple II compatability mode.
\par 
                    (Real men fight with wireframes)

\par
}
