{
K{\footnote K Jumping From Plane to Plane}
${\footnote $ Jumping From Plane to Plane}
#{\footnote # loc80}
{\b \fs24 Jumping from Plane to Plane}
\pard \plain \qj \fs20 \f0
\par
Pressing {\b <TAB>} or selecting {\b Next Aircraft} from the Special 
Menu will miraculously transport you into the cockpit of the next available 
aircraft (whether friend or foe). It's a good idea to first engage your own 
Autopilot {\b A} key before leaving. To take control, disengage the Autopilot 
and fly away. If you get bored or shot up, just skip to another 
plane. You can't go wrong!
} 
{\plain \page}

{
${\footnote $ Outside View}
K{\footnote K Outside View}
{\b \fs24 Outside View}\plain\par\par
#{\footnote # loc60}
\pard \plain \qj \fs20 \f0 
\{bmc hlpoutsv.bmp\}
\par
\par
Pressing the {\b 6} key or selecting {\b Outside} from the 
View Menu gives you a view outside your airplane. The following 
keys can be used to alter this view: 
{
 \pard \plain \f1 \fs10
\par
{\b i} ................ Decrease distance
\par
{\b u} ................ Increase distance
\par
{\b y} ................ horiziontal clockwise rotation
\par
{\b m} ................ horizontal counter-clockwise rotation
\par
{\b z} ................ vertical clockwise rotation
\par
{\b o} ................ vertical counter-clockwise rotation
}

} 
{\plain \page}

{
K{\footnote K Target Track}
${\footnote $ Target Track}
#{\footnote # loc61}
{\b \fs24 Target Track}
\pard \plain \qj \fs20 \f0
\par 
\{bmc hlptgtv.bmp\}
\par
Pressing the {\b 7} key or selecting {\b Target Track} from the View 
Menu gives you a most useful view in which the target aircraft you selected 
via the {\b <ENTER>} is displayed in the center of the screen, along 
with your airplane so you can quickly see your relationship to it. 
} 
{\plain \page}

{
K{\footnote K Target Track II}
${\footnote $ Target Track II}
#{\footnote # loc62}
{\b \fs24 Target Track II}
\pard \plain \qj \fs20 \f0 
\par
\{bmc hlptgtv2.bmp\}
\par
Pressing the {\b 8} key or selecting {\b Target Track II} from the View 
Menu gives you a look at your opponent's plane, with your plane  
in the center of the screen. This view is useful for selecting targets in a 
multi-bogey situation. Use the {\b <ENTER>} key to cycle through the various 
aircraft involved in the fight, selecting one which you wish to engage. 
}
{\plain \page}

